		"description": "<p>You have some inherent magical talent, and you have also decided to study magical lore. Whether this is curiosity, ambition, or a desire to understand yourself better, only you can say. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Intelligence or Charisma score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>When you would learn an @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.7jxnq4in81dmi93t]{Arcane Innovation} or @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.1u4hyjbgjmvl22js]{Elective Study}, you can choose freely from either list.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with the Arcana skill, or another skill from the sorcerer or wizard list if you are already proficient.</li>\n<li>You learn one of the following languages: draconic, sylvan, infernal, celestial, or primordial.</li>\n<li>While you are wielding an arcane spellcasting focus, you gain an expertise die on Intelligence and Charisma saves.</li>\n</ul>",
